<strong>Aim:</strong></p>

<p>Investigate the factors involved in the design of automotive radiators. Establish a relation between the rate heat rejection and the area of the radiator core.</p>

<p><strong>Summary:</strong></p>

<p>Used the <em>Number of Transfer Units (NTU)</em> method to relate the area of the core with the rate of heat rejection. Analysed experimental data and conducted a comparative study between these values and the predicted values from experiments to validate the result.</p>

<p>Conducted CFD simulations of thermal stress tests on <em>OpenSim</em> and analysed the temperature gradient, stresses and strain to validate new designs of automotive radiators.</p>

<p><strong>Attachments:</strong></p>

<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/pdf.js/2.16.105/pdf.min.js"></script>

<div class="pdf-thumbnail-container">
  
</div>

<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
    document.querySelectorAll(".pdf-thumbnail").forEach((canvas) => {
      const url = canvas.getAttribute("data-url");

      pdfjsLib.getDocument(url).promise.then(pdf => {
        return pdf.getPage(1);
      }).then(page => {
        const desiredWidth = 200; // Adjust this to control thumbnail width
        const viewport = page.getViewport({ scale: 1 }); // Default scale (1) to get original width

        const scale = desiredWidth / viewport.width; // Calculate scale based on desired width
        const scaledViewport = page.getViewport({ scale });

        const context = canvas.getContext("2d");

        // Set canvas size to match the scaled page
        canvas.width = scaledViewport.width;
        canvas.height = scaledViewport.height;

        const renderContext = {
          canvasContext: context,
          viewport: scaledViewport
        };

        return page.render(renderContext).promise;
      });

      canvas.addEventListener("click", () => {
        window.open(url, "_blank");
      });
    });
  });
</script>

